People have also known that white rabbit meat is low in cholesterol content. It, therefore, appeals to the health-conscious segment of meat consumers.
The legalisation of urban farming has also contributed to increased rabbit farming. Rabbits require very little space due to their small size and good social character.
It is rare to find rabbits fighting each other over food, water or space. They nonetheless do fight for mates.
In addition to occupying a small fraction of the space occupied by other livestock, rabbits can be housed in stacked up hutches that may be fixed or movable. Unlike chickens, rabbits are less fragile to diseases.



