Rabbits are very small in comparison to other livestock mammals. I refer to them as the miniature livestock.
The biggest challenge with tiny animals is that they tend to eat a lot, pass a lot of faeces and urine.
Consequently, they have a lot of demand for the maintenance of cleanliness and hygiene of their production units. Many farmers miss this aspect of rabbit production and end up paying dearly.
Good hygiene
I visited a farmer in Nairobi two weeks ago who said her rabbits kept getting sick and dying. The compound was saturated with rabbit smell.
She was concerned neighbours would start complaining. “Is it possible to keep rabbits without the smell?” she inquired.



