Plant matter of high quality and nutrition could also replace the commercial feed. Clean drinking water should be provided at all times for the rabbits to drink at will.
The living environment should be clean, hygienic, dry and well-ventilated. Rabbits should not be overcrowded.
Finally, I informed Mary that dirty housing produces strong rabbit odour that taints the rabbit meat and makes it unpalatable and unsuitable for the market.
